WEBVTT

00:08:27.117 --> 00:08:30.633
that would include
a sort of hopeful future.

00:08:30.657 --> 00:08:32.668
And he made a heroic attempt at doing so,

00:08:32.692 --> 00:08:36.044
and I'm not sure he really came up
with anything that quite did that.

00:08:36.068 --> 00:08:38.727
I mean, it's just much more
compelling when it's creepy.

00:08:38.751 --> 00:08:42.388
"Black Mirror" is an amazing
TV series, and it's creepy.

00:08:42.412 --> 00:08:43.774
SP: Yeah.

00:08:43.798 --> 00:08:47.518
And there is a kind of asymmetry
in our moral perceptions,

00:08:47.542 --> 00:08:50.492
as financial writer
Morgan Housel pointed out,

00:08:50.516 --> 00:08:52.966
pessimists sound like
they're trying to help you,

00:08:52.990 --> 00:08:55.799
optimists sound like
they're trying to sell you something.

00:08:57.744 --> 00:08:59.141
It's a tough sell.

00:08:59.165 --> 00:09:02.458
CA: So, Steve, I ask you this:
Are you trying to sell us something?